Too often is it said that football should follow rugby's example in many aspects of the game, but on this occasion they most certainly should.

Suarez received a 10-match ban from the FA for biting Chelsea' Branislav Ivanovic last year and a seven-game suspension for sinking his teeth into PSV Eindhoven's Otman Bakkal while he was at Ajax.

If you add those two together then you would still be nowhere near the length of the ban that should be given out.

For a persistent offender the retribution must be severe.

A four-year ban like in rugby? Maybe not quite, but FIFA should be thinking in terms of years and months, not weeks, when they serve Suarez's sentence.

